headline: Is DoorDash’s Drone Delivery Ambitions Changing the Stock’s Outlook in 2025?
summary: Deciding what to do with DoorDash stock right now? You are not alone. After another big year, DoorDash’s shares are up a stunning 59.7% year to date and 81.9% over the past 12 months, investors are weighing how much more room there is to run. There has definitely been some bumpiness along the way, too. Just last week the stock pulled back by 3%, even as excitement continues about where DoorDash is headed. Among the moves catching investors’ eyes: the company is pushing further into autonomous...

headline: Underdog Named #3 Startup in U.S. by LinkedIn
summary: BROOKLYN, N.Y., October 15, 2025--Underdog, the fastest-growing sports company in the U.S., today was named the number three startup on the 2025 LinkedIn Top 50 Startups List in the U.S., up from number 15 in 2024. This is the third consecutive year Underdog has made LinkedIn’s Top 50 Startups List, recognizing the company for its rapid employment growth, job interest and attraction of top talent. Underdog is the only sports company to make the list this year.
